  "body": "On the release page, a signed `checksums.txt` file is provided to users. However there are no instructions in the release notes or the README file for how to verify this signed file, including where to download the PGP key used to sign this file. After some searching, I found instructions on the [MyCrypto blog](https://medium.com/mycrypto/announcing-the-mycrypto-desktop-alpha-release-44e09f8b3248) but I think these instructions / at least a link to the key could be put in the release notes and/or README file too.",
